msContents.summary: Substantial sections from an illustrated treatise titled Book of the balance of wisdom, which concerns measurement of weight, with a historical introduction to theories of gravity and weighing in Greek and Arabic science; tables of densities of substances including metals, precious stones, solids, and liquids; and descriptions of different types of balances. A few marginal notes are present. A few catchwords and some minuscule letters under undotted letters have been added by later hands. Damage to edges of many leaves.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh script, with headings in larger riqa' script.

decoDesc.decoNote: 26 diagrams and 18 tables in red and black ink.

binding.p: Unbound, with some partial gatherings still joined or repaired at gutter.

origin.p: Written ca. 1270 (based on paper and script).

history.provenance: Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd., cat. 22 (2000), to Lawrence J. Schoenberg.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2011.
